1. Download Maven:

Go to the Apache Maven website - https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi
Download the binary zip archive (e.g. apache-maven-3.9.9-bin.zip).

2. Extract the Archive:

Extract the downloaded zip file to a directory of your choice (e.g., C:\Program Files\Apache\maven).

3. Set Environment Variables:

Search for "Environment Variables" in the Start menu.
Under "System Variables," click "New" to add a new variable:
Variable name: MAVEN_HOME
Variable value: The path to your Maven folder (e.g., C:\Program Files\Apache\maven\apache-maven-3.x.x).
Find the Path variable in the "System Variables" section, select it, and click "Edit."
Add a new entry: %MAVEN_HOME%\bin.

4.Verify the Installation:

Open Command Prompt and run:
mvn -version
You should see the version of Maven displayed.

5. Navigate to Your Project Directory: 
Open your command line interface and navigate to the root directory of your Maven project:

6. Identify the Test Class: 
Locate the specific test class you want to run. For example, 
letâ€™s say your test class is named MySeleniumTest.


7. Run test using maven for Testng
mvn -Dtest=MySeleniumTest test
